# Garage Admin API examples
# Requires VS Code REST Client extension
# Set @adminToken to the value in your .garage-credentials file
# (or check garage.toml for admin_token)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3903
@adminToken = YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Cluster status
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/GetClusterStatus
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### List buckets
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/ListBuckets
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### List keys
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/ListKeys
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Garage version info
GET {{baseUrl}}/version
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Metrics (Prometheus format)
# Use metrics_token from garage.toml
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_METRICS_TOKEN_HERE
